The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Muktsar, Sept. 10 (PTI): A MiG 21 aircraft of the Indian Air Force today crashed in Punjabs Muktsar district, killing the pilot.           
	The fighter plane, on a routine sortie, had taken off from the Bhatinda airbase. It crashed at Bhaliana village, killing Flight Lieutenant Manu Akhori on the spot.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The CBI on Thursday recorded the statement of Buta Singh, chairman of the National Commission for Scheduled Castes, in connection with a bribery case involving his son. The former Union minister was quizzed by a two-member team at his office. Buta had agreed to be questioned after the CBI said he was required as a witness and was not an accused.                   
	 Islamabad (PTI): ISI chief Lt Gen Ahmed Shuja Pasha attended an iftar dinner hosted by Indian high commissioner Sharat Sabharwal in Islamabad on Thursday. Observers said Pashas decision to attend the event was a strong signal, in view of the strained ties between the two countries. Pasha told Sabharwal there should be more interaction.                   
	 Jaipur (PTI): A medical officer has been arrested for allegedly demanding sexual favours from a nurse who had come to him to verify her medical bills. Dr Subir Moitra was picked up from his home on Wednesday.                  
	 Calcutta: Bengal finance minister Asim Dasgupta said on Thursday that potato brought from Punjab would be sold tomorrow at ration shops in Calcutta and its neighbouring areas in North and South 24-Parganas and Hooghly.                   
	 Malappuram (PTI): Several flights from Gulf countries were delayed on Thursday as fog disrupted air traffic for three hours at the international airport at Karippur in Kozhikode. Most of these flights were diverted to Chennai and Kochi airports, but arrived in Karippur after the skies cleared.                                                                                                                           
